  "text": "Volume of ejaculate was similar in both racial groups during all seasons of the year and these values agree with the ranges obtained by other authors in Bos indicus and Bos taurus bulls [CITATION_1] Koivisto et al., 2009) . It has been reported that seasonal effects can be observed in volume of ejaculate of bulls by a combined effect of high temperatures and poor grazing quality in the dry and hot season (Koivisto et al., 2009) . Such was not the case of the animals in the present study, since all bulls were fed adequately. On the other hand, it has been demonstrated that the ejaculate volume, but not the sperm concentration and motility, is significantly influenced by the semen collection team and the ejaculator device used [CITATION_2] . Through the present study, collection conditions were standardized and semen was collected by the same technician with the same equipment in such way that the procedure was carried out similarly every time.",
